colorjs
==============

Basic color analysis with javascript using canvas, finds the luminance and colors in an image element

usage
--------------
After including colorjs.js:

    <script type="text/javascript" src="colorjs.js" />

In your page,

    var image_element = document.getElementById("image_id");
    var color = analyze_color(image_element);

The results look like this:

    {
        avg: [r, g, b],
        color_style: "rgb(r, g, b)",
        lum: lum
    }

Where r, g, and b are the rgb components of the average color, and lum is
the Y value/luminance.
